         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="vol-2-B_M-d2e3165-person" n="vol-2-B_M-Eleazar-12">
               <sex cert="high">M</sex>
               <persName type="lemma">אלעזר</persName>
               <persName type="lemma" xml:lang="en">Eleazar</persName>–<state type="desc">
                  <note>Hoshaiah (1)’s son</note>
               </state>
               <state type="provenance">
                  <note>–</note>
               </state>
               <bibl>yBer5:2, 9b (Kosovsky,Yerushalmi, 69)</bibl>
               <state type="addl-Descr">
                  <note>Fictitious?<ref type="note" corresp="#d2e3188"/>
                  </note>
               </state>
               <floruit>Pre-400<ref type="note" corresp="#d2e3198"/>
               </floruit>
               <note xml:id="d2e3188" n="30"> This person is only
                            mentioned once (here) in the form ר' אלעזר ב"ר הושעיה. Elsewhere in PT
                            we find the formula ר' אלעזר בשם ר' הושעיה (Rabbi Eleazar in the name of
                            Rabbi Hoshaiah). Also Hyman does not record him. Yet in all the mss
                            (Leiden, Vatican Paris, London) and in the Venice print here the first
                            form is recorded. Only in the margins of the Leiden Ms is the text
                            emended. I think this form is the
                            lectio difficilior,but
                            doubt lingers.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e3198" n="31"> Mentioned in a Palestinian-amoraic source with no
                            chronological context, see Introduction 7.4.4.</note>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
